The management of Federal Polytechnic, Ado Ekiti, said on Sunday that the institution would leave no stone unturned in ensuring it turned around its economic fortunes and transform into a centre of excellence. The management said that as part of efforts to achieve the feat, it had convoked a two-day Economic Summit with the theme, “Motivation, productivity, and institutional progress: The challenge of harnessing the potentials of The Federal Polytechnic, Ado-Ekiti”. billed for Monday and Tuesday. It stated that the Stakeholders’ Retreat was projected to turn around the economic fortunes of the institution. A statement by an FPA official, Kayode Adebusuyi, on behalf of the Director, Protocol, Information and Public Relations, Ade Adeyemi-Adejolu, said Ekiti State Governor Kayode Fayemi and the founder, Afe Babalola University, Ado Ekiti, Aare Afe Babalola, were among dignitaries expected at the retreat. Adeyemi-Adejolu stated, “The summit, is also expected to bring about efficiency in the delivery of service, effective capacity utilization and the attainment of the objective of the polytechnic, thereby improving the economic fortunes and transforming the institution into a centre of excellence in teaching, research and learning.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com